        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 8:41PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 840 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Chilhowie, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glade Spring, Damascus, and Konnarock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
